result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Christopher M Martell in court.  Kristi J Gordon appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  The Defendant files the waiver of attorney form and wants to proceed to dispose of the case today.  The Defendant is sworn in and questioned by the Court.  The Court finds the Defendant is competent to represent himself and to proceed without counsel.   The charge is dismissed and read into 15CM1635.

Filed by the Defendant requesting to reschedule hearing.  
The Defendant later followed up with a phone call to advise Court he is now able to appear at hearing.
Defendant is not to use/possess any controlled substances without a valid prescription and take as prescribed.  Defendant not to possess any drug paraphernalia.

Defendant Christopher M Martell in court.  Pablo Galaviz appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court advises of right to an attorney.  NOT GUILTY PLEA ENTERED BY COURT.
